<seg id="1">(During its centennial year, The Wall Street Journal will report events of the past century that stand as milestones of American business history.)</seg>
<seg id="2">Thomas Jefferson sold Congress on the idea of the decimal system for currency, thus saving Americans the headaches of pounds, shillings and pence.</seg>
<seg id="3">But he struck out with the decimal system of metric weights and measures the French had invented.</seg>
<seg id="4">Instead, Congress opted for the inches, feet and yards the colonists had brought with them.</seg>
