<seg id="1">President Bush and Soviet leader Mikhail Gorbachev will hold an informal meeting in early December, a move that should give both leaders a political boost at home.</seg>
<seg id="2">The White House is purposely not calling the meeting a summit so that there won't be any expectation of detailed negotiations or agreements.</seg>
